The paper deals with the task of detecting interest points in 3D meshes, which is a problem related to computer vision (CV) and computer graphics (GR). The authors propose a machine learning approach using a random forest classifier, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the authors also mention a new benchmark for evaluating their method, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (MM).
